The Senate has confirmed Omolola Kuburat Abiola Edewor as the Executive Director, Corporate Services, of the Nigeria Deposit Insurance Corporation (NDIC). Kuburat, the daughter of late Chief M.K.O. Abiola, was confirmed following the adoption of the report of the Committee on Banking, Insurance and other Financial Institutions at yesterday’s plenary. The chairman of the committee, Sen Rafiu Ibrahim (PDP, Kwara) told his colleagues prior to the adoption of the report that Kuburat appeared before the committee for screening. He said the committee found her worthy of being re-appointed to the position for second term, which she will serve in the next five years. When Senate President Bukola Saraki subjected her confirmation to a voice vote, all the senators present supported it. Senate confirms Abiola’s daughter as NDIC Executive Director Buhari nominates Abike as Diaspora Commission chief Drama as Senate confirms Keyamo as NDIC member